  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dd2 6\u0d9a \u0d85\u0db6\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2  \u0dbb\u0dda\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "6 Crore Abili gets stuck in customs",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to Customs Media Spokesperson Mr. Sudatta Silva, Director of Customs, 10 twenty-foot containers containing scrap metal worth over 6 crore rupees, which an Indian businessman tried to illegally export from the country, were seized by the officers of the Central Intelligence Division of Sri Lanka Customs.",
        "Customs says that 140 metric tons of scrap copper, aluminum and iron were found in those ten containers and that these containers contained 140 metric tons of natural crepe rubber in the customs declaration submitted by the exporter to Sri Lanka Customs.",
        "The Customs stated that three suspects have been arrested and remanded in custody regarding this illegal export. The Central Intelligence Division of the Sri Lanka Customs is conducting further investigations on this matter."
      ],
